FBIS4-37137 "drnes117_j_94011" FBIS-NES-94-117 Daily Report 17 Jun 1994 ARABIAN PENINSULA Yemen Aden Citizens Warned To Avoid Strategic Locations Aden Citizens Warned To Avoid Strategic Locations JN1706053394 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 0505 GMT 17 Jun 94 JN1706053394 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network Arabic BFN [Text] Statement and warning issued by the Aden Axis Command to the brother citizens in the city of Aden: In the name of God, the merciful, the compassionate. The Aden Axis Command warns and draws the attention of the brother citizens in Aden to avoid the following areas: Aden airport, Badr Camp, the naval forces berth, the radio and television buildings, the operations center in al-Sawwahi in the so-called Defense Ministry, the [Yemeni Socialist Party] Central Committee headquarters, al-Ma'ashiq area, and all the camps inside Aden, out of concern for the safety of all citizens and their precious lives. The forces of unity and constitutional legitimacy will have to deal with these positions and camps because the gang of rebellion against the constitutional legitimacy is not abiding by the cease-fire and continues to attack the positions and camps of the forces of unity and legitimacy. The Aden Axis Command is confident that all honorable brother citizens in Aden will heed this appeal and warning and keep away from these positions and camps.
